#
# HOW THIS WORKS
# GitHub reads this file top-to-bottom. The LAST matching rule wins.
# Every PR that touches a matching path will require approval from the
# listed owner(s) before it can merge — even if branch protection is set
# to "1 required reviewer". This file makes YOU the required reviewer
# for everything, and adds extra requirements on the most sensitive paths.
#
# HOW TO SET THIS UP
# 1. Replace @Aaks-hatH below with your actual GitHub username.
# 2. Commit this file to .github/CODEOWNERS on your main branch.
# 3. Go to Settings → Branches → Edit your main branch protection rule.
#    ✅ Check "Require review from Code Owners"
# 4. That's it. GitHub enforces it automatically on every PR.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── DEFAULT: You must approve every single PR, on every file ──────────────────
